      "side": 1,
      "message": "strictly speaking it is possible that two RCPs from same client end up racing and hitting this code. For example:\n1. The client makes an RPC and waits for a reply.\n2. The backend server starts processing it.\n3. The connection between the client and the frontend drops, the client initiates a retry.\n4. Meanwhile the backend is still processing previous RPC.\n5. Now the backend handles two RegisterPrefix RPC from same client concurrently.\n\nSo consider adding OpNonce check here too.",
